<div id="youth" class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
            <div class="page-header">
                <h2> Youth</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Youth are the Country’s future. We must help them to be ready to take the role of family.

                Their development will not be left to RANDOM.

                Hence all children, youth up to 21 years all Youth are Properly and Completely engaged either in Studying, Learning Trades, Employed or in further development in a suitable Disciplined Environment.

                There is no room for idling for youth but will be developed to meet their future needs.

                There will be curfew for MINORS after 6 pm unless they are accompanied by their parents or guardians and not strangers, brother or sisters. This is to protect them who cannot protect themselves.

                Children will stay with the parents until 18 years of age.  The parents will be paid allowance to meet the demands of having them.

                All children under foster care will be allowed to continue to live in those arrangements until they are ready to move.

            </p>
